```json
{
  "application": "OpenFOAM",
  "software_requirements": [
    "OpenFOAM 2306",
    "Python virtual environment with pyfoam package",
    "pyFoamPlotWatcher",
    "pyFoamClearCase"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": {
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks": 40,
    "cpus_per_task": 1,
    "memory": "not specified"
  }
}
```

This script uses OpenFOAM for computational fluid dynamics simulations. It utilizes a Python virtual environment with the `pyfoam` package, which includes the `pyFoamPlotWatcher` and `pyFoamClearCase` utilities for post-processing and case management.

The script specifies resource requirements: 1 node, 40 tasks, and 1 CPU per task. While it doesn't explicitly define memory requirements, you can set them using `--mem` or `--mem-per-cpu` in the `SBATCH` options.
